From 031592641197d2f86f4017201b17f4f1880166ae Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: =?UTF-8?q?Felix=20Paul=20K=C3=BChne?= <felix@feepk.net>
Date: Mon, 6 Jul 2026 10:31:44 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 20/21] package/apple: append -simulator to the xros target
 triple

Commit 52d4078f58 (package/apple: set the proper C flag to target xros)
replaced the previously-empty xros CFLAG with an unconditional device
target triple. This broke simulator builds: objects compiled for
visionOS-simulator failed to link against the device target (ld:
building for 'visionOS', but linking in object file built for
'visionOS-simulator').

Append the -simulator suffix when building for the simulator, matching
the behaviour the empty CFLAG got implicitly from the SDK.
---
 extras/package/apple/build.sh | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/extras/package/apple/build.sh b/extras/package/apple/build.sh
index ce4c1645bd..b8b9e0bca7 100755
--- a/extras/package/apple/build.sh
+++ b/extras/package/apple/build.sh
@@ -218,6 +218,9 @@ set_deployment_target()
         VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET_LDFLAG="${VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET_CFLAG}"
     else
         VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET_CFLAG="--target=${VLC_HOST_ARCH}-apple-xros${VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET}"
+        if [ -n "$VLC_HOST_PLATFORM_SIMULATOR" ]; then
+            VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET_CFLAG="${VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET_CFLAG}-simulator"
+        fi
         VLC_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET_LDFLAG=""
     fi
 }
